            <title>[THRIFT-720] HTTPClientTransport ignores url parameters</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-720</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I recently ran into a situation where I had to pass a parameter to a thrift http endpoint, but noticed that HTTPClientTransport was ignoring it when sending the request.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;client = HTTPClientTransport.new(&apos;http://www.foo.com/my/service?param=value&quot;)&lt;br/&gt;
client.do_something&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;will post to &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.foo.com/my/service&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.foo.com/my/service&lt;/a&gt; instead of &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.foo.com/my/service?param=value&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.foo.com/my/service?param=value&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
